  "doc_id": "35598",
  "text": "Both eZiPro and bZiPro show two sets of cross-peaks for NS2B [CITATION_1] which was attributed to the release of NS2B from the NS2B-NS3pro complex . Greater stability of the protease would be expected for the classical construct containing the Gly 4 -Ser-Gly 4 linker. This construct (referred to as gZiPro) has not been studied by NMR spectroscopy in the same detail as the unlinked constructs eZiPro and bZiPro. It showed no change of the NMR spectrum with the classical protease inhibitor BPTI, suggesting that the covalent linkage prevents binding of the inhibitor .",
